Customer module#

class Customer.Customer(customer_id, username, first_name, last_name, email, phone_number=None)#

Bases: object

Represents a customer in the stock trading game.

Parameters:

  • customer_id (int) – The unique ID of the customer.

  • username (str) – The username of the customer.

  • first_name (str) – The first name of the customer.

  • last_name (str) – The last name of the customer.

  • phone_number (str or None) – The phone number of the customer (optional).

  • email (str) – The email address of the customer.

Raises:

  • ValueError – If the customer ID is not a positive integer.

  • ValueError – If any of the required parameters (username, first_name, last_name, email) are empty strings.

Usage:

customer = Customer(customer_id=1, username=’jdoe’, first_name=’John’, last_name=’Doe’, phone_number=’123-456-7890’, email=’jdoe@example.com’)
